  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="Aink263-kilavi">varaiviṭai vaittup pirinta talaimakaṉ mīṇṭamai yaṟinta talaimakaḷ nī tolainta nalam iṉṟ eytiya kāraṇam eṉṉai yeṉṟa tōḻikkuc colliyatu. 
          </p>
        <p xml:lang="en">
          What the heroine, who knew of the return of the hero who had [earlier] fixed the time of marriage and separated, told the confidante who asked, “For what reason has the goodness you had lost been regained today?”
          
        </p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="Aink263">
<l>naṉpo ṉaṉṉa puṉiṟutī rēṉal</l>
<l>kaṭṭaḷai yaṉṉa kēḻaṉ māntuṅ</l>
<l>kuṉṟukeḻu nāṭaṉ ṟāṉum</l>
<l>vantaṉaṉ vantaṉṟu tōḻiyeṉ ṉalaṉē</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
        <l>The man from the land of hills,</l>
        <l>on which boars, like touchstones,</l>
        <l>feed on ripened millets, like fine gold—</l>

        <l rend="space">he too has come.</l>
        <l>[And so] it has returned, O friend—my goodness.</l>
        
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
